      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The scientific community is deeply divided on the timeline and likelihood of true superintelligence, making the consensus highly speculative. While some leading AI researchers take the existential risk warnings very seriously, others argue that the current focus on \"AGI\" is premature science fiction. The grounded concerns are more readily found in the immediate dangers of misuse, like autonomous weapons, rather than the far-off scenario of a rogue god-like AI.",
